                  , on the king's highway, putting him in corporal fear and danger of his life, and taking from his person a pair of buckles plated with silver, value one shillings, a leather pocket-book, value three pence, a pair of leather gloves, value two pence, a green silk purse, value two pence, two silver pennies, one six-pence, one silver two-pence, a pair of crystal stone studs, set in silver, a cloth coat, value five shillings, and a hat, value five shillings, the property of the said Edward
            </rs>, <rs id="t17700221-6-cd33" type="crimeDate">Jan. 11</rs>
